name: chrome_ext
comment: A library to expose the Chrome ext APIs.

class.name: AlarmCreateInfo
class.preview: todo(mpcomplete): rename to CreateInfo when http://crbug.com/123073 is fixed.

class.name: BookmarkTreeNode
class.preview: A node (either a bookmark or a folder) in the bookmark tree. Child nodes are ordered within their parent folder.

class.name: OnChildrenReorderedEvent
class.preview: Fired when the children of a folder have changed their order due to the order being sorted in the UI. This is not called as a result of a move().

class.name: BookmarksOnMovedEvent
class.preview: Fired when a bookmark or folder is moved to a different parent folder.

class.name: BookmarksOnChangedEvent
class.preview: Fired when a bookmark or folder changes. <b>Note:</b> Currently, only title and url changes trigger this.

class.name: BookmarksOnRemovedEvent
class.preview: Fired when a bookmark or folder is removed. When a folder is removed recursively, a single notification is fired for the folder, and none for its contents.

class.name: OnCreatedEvent
class.preview: Fired when a bookmark or folder is created.

class.name: ImageDataType
class.preview: Pixel data for an image. Must be an ImageData object (for example, from a canvas element).

class.name: DataTypeSet
class.preview: A set of data types. Missing data types are interpreted as false.

class.name: RemovalOptions
class.preview: Options that determine exactly what data will be removed.

class.name: ResourceIdentifier
class.preview: The only content type using resource identifiers is contentSettings.plugins. For more information, see Resource Identifiers.

class.name: OnClickData
class.preview: Information sent when a context menu item is clicked.

class.name: OnClickedEvent
class.preview: Fired when a context menu item is clicked.

class.name: CookieStore
class.preview: Represents a cookie store in the browser. An incognito mode window, for instance, uses a separate cookie store from a non-incognito window.

class.name: Cookie
class.preview: Represents information about an HTTP cookie.

class.name: TargetInfo
class.preview: Debug target information

class.name: Debuggee
class.preview: Debuggee identifier. Either tabId or extensionId must be specified

class.name: OnDetachEvent
class.preview: Fired when browser terminates debugging session for the tab. This happens when either the tab is being closed or Chrome DevTools is being invoked for the attached tab.

class.name: OnEventEvent
class.preview: Fired whenever debugging target issues instrumentation event.

class.name: ShowPageAction
class.preview: Declarative event action that shows the extension's [][pageAction page action] while the corresponding conditions are met. This action can be used without host permissions, but the extension must have a page action. If the extension takes the activeTab permission, a click on the page action will grant access to the active tab.

class.name: PageStateMatcher
class.preview: Matches the state of a web page by various criteria.

class.name: RemoveResponseCookie
class.preview: Removes one or more cookies of response. Note that it is preferred to use the Cookies API because this is computationally less expensive.

class.name: RemoveRequestCookie
class.preview: Removes one or more cookies of request. Note that it is preferred to use the Cookies API because this is computationally less expensive.

class.name: EditResponseCookie
class.preview: Edits one or more cookies of response. Note that it is preferred to use the Cookies API because this is computationally less expensive.

class.name: EditRequestCookie
class.preview: Edits one or more cookies of request. Note that it is preferred to use the Cookies API because this is computationally less expensive.

class.name: AddResponseCookie
class.preview: Adds a cookie to the response or overrides a cookie, in case another cookie of the same name exists already. Note that it is preferred to use the Cookies API because this is computationally less expensive.

class.name: AddRequestCookie
class.preview: Adds a cookie to the request or overrides a cookie, in case another cookie of the same name exists already. Note that it is preferred to use the Cookies API because this is computationally less expensive.

class.name: FilterResponseCookie
class.preview: A filter of a cookie in HTTP Responses.

class.name: ResponseCookie
class.preview: A specification of a cookie in HTTP Responses.

class.name: RequestCookie
class.preview: A filter or specification of a cookie in HTTP Requests.

class.name: SendMessageToExtension
class.preview: Triggers the declarativeWebRequest.onMessage event.

class.name: IgnoreRules
class.preview: Masks all rules that match the specified criteria.

class.name: RemoveResponseHeader
class.preview: Removes all response headers of the specified names and values.

class.name: AddResponseHeader
class.preview: Adds the response header to the response of this web request. As multiple response headers may share the same name, you need to first remove and then add a new response header in order to replace one.

class.name: RemoveRequestHeader
class.preview: Removes the request header of the specified name. Do not use SetRequestHeader and RemoveRequestHeader with the same header name on the same request. Each request header name occurs only once in each request.

class.name: SetRequestHeader
class.preview: Sets the request header of the specified name to the specified value. If a header with the specified name did not exist before, a new one is created. Header name comparison is always case-insensitive. Each request header name occurs only once in each request.

class.name: RedirectByRegEx
class.preview: Redirects a request by applying a regular expression on the URL. The regular expressions use the RE2 syntax.

class.name: RedirectToEmptyDocument
class.preview: Declarative event action that redirects a network request to an empty document.

class.name: RedirectToTransparentImage
class.preview: Declarative event action that redirects a network request to a transparent image.

class.name: RedirectRequest
class.preview: Declarative event action that redirects a network request.

class.name: CancelRequest
class.preview: Declarative event action that cancels a network request.

class.name: RequestMatcher
class.preview: Matches network events by various criteria.

class.name: HeaderFilter
class.preview: Filters request headers for various criteria. Multiple criteria are evaluated as a conjunction.

class.name: DesktopCaptureSourceType
class.preview: Enum used to define set of desktop media sources used in chooseDesktopMedia(). enum of screen, window, tab

class.name: Button
class.preview: A button created by the extension.

class.name: ExtensionSidebarPane
class.preview: A sidebar created by the extension.

class.name: ExtensionPanel
class.preview: Represents a panel created by extension.

class.name: ElementsPanel
class.preview: Represents the Elements panel.

class.name: ChromeDevtoolsPanels
class.preview: Use the chrome.devtools.panels API to integrate your extension into Developer Tools window UI: create your own panels, access existing panels, and add sidebars.

class.name: GetRequestContentResult
class.preview: The return type for getContent.

class.name: Request
class.preview: Represents a network request for a document resource (script, image and so on). See HAR Specification for reference.

class.name: ChromeDevtoolsNetwork
class.preview: Use the chrome.devtools.network API to retrieve the information about network requests displayed by the Developer Tools in the Network panel.

class.name: GetResourceContentResult
class.preview: The return type for getContent.

class.name: EvalResult
class.preview: The return type for eval.

class.name: Resource
class.preview: A resource within the inspected page, such as a document, a script, or an image.

class.name: OnResourceContentCommittedEvent
class.preview: Fired when a new revision of the resource is committed (e.g. user saves an edited version of the resource in the Developer Tools).

class.name: ChromeDevtoolsInspectedWindow
class.preview: Use the chrome.devtools.inspectedWindow API to interact with the inspected window: obtain the tab ID for the inspected page, evaluate the code in the context of the inspected window, reload the page, or obtain the list of resources within the page.

class.name: DownloadDelta
class.preview: Encapsulates a change in a DownloadItem.

class.name: DownloadItem
class.preview: The state of the process of downloading a file.

class.name: State
class.preview: Comment preview not available

class.name: DangerType
class.preview: Comment preview not available

class.name: FilenameConflictAction
class.preview: Comment preview not available

class.name: UrlFilter
class.preview: Filters URLs for various criteria. See event filtering. All criteria are case sensitive.

class.name: ChromeEvent
class.preview: An object which allows the addition and removal of listeners for a Chrome event.

class.name: Rule
class.preview: Description of a declarative rule for handling events.

class.name: OnRequestExternalEvent
class.preview: Deprecated: please use onMessageExternal.

class.name: OnRequestEvent
class.preview: Deprecated: please use onMessage.

class.name: FileHandlerExecuteEventDetails
class.preview: Event details payload for fileBrowserHandler.onExecute event.

class.name: OnExecuteEvent
class.preview: Fired when file system action is executed from ChromeOS file browser.

class.name: LevelOfControl
class.preview: One of<br>not_controllable: cannot be controlled by any extension<br>[controlled_by_other_extensions]: controlled by extensions with higher precedence<br>[controllable_by_this_extension]: can be controlled by this extension<br>[controlled_by_this_extension]: controlled by this extension enum of not_controllable, controlled_by_other_extensions, controllable_by_this_extension, controlled_by_this_extension

class.name: GenericFamily
class.preview: A CSS generic font family. enum of standard, sansserif, serif, fixed, cursive, fantasy

class.name: ScriptCode
class.preview: An ISO 15924 script code. The default, or global, script is represented by script code "Zyyy". enum of Afak, Arab, Armi, Armn, Avst, Bali, Bamu, Bass, Batk, Beng, Blis, Bopo, Brah, Brai, Bugi, Buhd, Cakm, Cans, Cari, Cham, Cher, Cirt, Copt, Cprt, Cyrl, Cyrs, Deva, Dsrt, Dupl, Egyd, Egyh, Egyp, Elba, Ethi, Geor, Geok, Glag, Goth, Gran, Grek, Gujr, Guru, Hang, Hani, Hano, Hans, Hant, Hebr, Hluw, Hmng, Hung, Inds, Ital, Java, Jpan, Jurc, Kali, Khar, Khmr, Khoj, Knda, Kpel, Kthi, Lana, Laoo, Latf, Latg, Latn, Lepc, Limb, Lina, Linb, Lisu, Loma, Lyci, Lydi, Mand, Mani, Maya, Mend, Merc, Mero, Mlym, Moon, Mong, Mroo, Mtei, Mymr, Narb, Nbat, Nkgb, Nkoo, Nshu, Ogam, Olck, Orkh, Orya, Osma, Palm, Perm, Phag, Phli, Phlp, Phlv, Phnx, Plrd, Prti, Rjng, Roro, Runr, Samr, Sara, Sarb, Saur, Sgnw, Shaw, Shrd, Sind, Sinh, Sora, Sund, Sylo, Syrc, Syre, Syrj, Syrn, Tagb, Takr, Tale, Talu, Taml, Tang, Tavt, Telu, Teng, Tfng, Tglg, Thaa, Thai, Tibt, Tirh, Ugar, Vaii, Visp, Wara, Wole, Xpeo, Xsux, Yiii, Zmth, Zsym, Zyyy

class.name: FontName
class.preview: Represents a font name.

class.name: VisitItem
class.preview: An object encapsulating one visit to a URL.

class.name: HistoryItem
class.preview: An object encapsulating one result of a history query.

class.name: MenuItem
class.preview: A menu item used by an input method to interact with the user from the language menu.

class.name: InputContext
class.preview: Describes an input Context

class.name: KeyboardEvent
class.preview: See http://www.w3.org/TR/DOM-Level-3-Events/#events-KeyboardEvent

class.name: OnSurroundingTextChangedEvent
class.preview: Called when the editable string around caret is changed or when the caret position is moved. The text length is limited to 100 characters for each back and forth direction.

class.name: OnMenuItemActivatedEvent
class.preview: Called when the user selects a menu item

class.name: OnCandidateClickedEvent
class.preview: This event is sent if this extension owns the active IME.

class.name: OnKeyEventEvent
class.preview: This event is sent if this extension owns the active IME.

class.name: ChromeInputIme
class.preview: Use the chrome.input.ime API to implement a custom IME for Chrome OS. This allows your extension to handle keystrokes, set the composition, and manage the candidate window.

class.name: WatchLocationRequestInfo
class.preview: Parameter of watchLocation call.

class.name: Location
class.preview: Parameter of onLocationUpdate event's listener.

class.name: Coordinates
class.preview: Coordinates part of the Location object.

class.name: ExtensionInfo
class.preview: Information about an installed extension, app, or theme.

class.name: IconInfo
class.preview: Information about an icon belonging to an extension, app, or theme.

class.name: DefaultSuggestResult
class.preview: A suggest result.

class.name: SuggestResult
class.preview: A suggest result.

class.name: OnInputEnteredEvent
class.preview: User has accepted what is typed into the omnibox.

class.name: OnInputChangedEvent
class.preview: User has changed what is typed into the omnibox.

class.name: Cache
class.preview: The Cache object contains information about the size and utilization of a cache used by the browser.

class.name: Process
class.preview: An object containing information about one of the browser's processes.

class.name: OnExitedEvent
class.preview: Fired each time a process is terminated, providing the type of exit.

class.name: ProxyConfig
class.preview: An object encapsulating a complete proxy configuration.

class.name: PacScript
class.preview: An object holding proxy auto-config information. Exactly one of the fields should be non-empty.

class.name: ProxyRules
class.preview: An object encapsulating the set of proxy rules for all protocols. Use either 'singleProxy' or (a subset of) 'proxyForHttp', 'proxyForHttps', 'proxyForFtp' and 'fallbackProxy'.

class.name: ProxyServer
class.preview: An object encapsulating a single proxy server's specification.

class.name: RequestUpdateCheckResult
class.preview: The return type for requestUpdateCheck.

class.name: MessageSender
class.preview: An object containing information about the script context that sent a message or request.

class.name: Port
class.preview: An object which allows two way communication with other pages.

class.name: OnMessageExternalEvent
class.preview: Fired when a message is sent from another extension/app. Cannot be used in a content script.

class.name: OnMessageEvent
class.preview: Fired when a message is sent from either an extension process or a content script.

class.name: StorageOnChangedEvent
class.preview: Fired when one or more items change.

class.name: ChromeSystemStorage
class.preview: Use the chrome.system.storage API to query storage device information and be notified when a removable storage device is attached and detached.

class.name: ChromeSystemNetwork
class.preview: Use the chrome.system.network API.

class.name: ChromeSystemMemory
class.preview: The chrome.system.memory API.

class.name: ChromeSystemDisplay
class.preview: Use the system.display API to query display metadata.

class.name: ChromeSystemCpu
class.preview: Use the system.cpu API to query CPU metadata.

class.name: CaptureOptions
class.preview: Whether we are requesting tab video and/or audio and the MediaTrackConstraints that should be set for these streams.

class.name: MediaStreamConstraint
class.preview: MediaTrackConstraints for the media streams that will be passed to WebRTC. See section on MediaTrackConstraints: http://dev.w3.org/2011/webrtc/editor/getusermedia.html

class.name: InjectDetails
class.preview: Details of the script or CSS to inject. Either the code or the file property must be set, but both may not be set at the same time.

class.name: OnReplacedEvent
class.preview: Fired when a tab is replaced with another tab due to prerendering or instant.

class.name: TabsOnRemovedEvent
class.preview: Fired when a tab is closed.

class.name: OnAttachedEvent
class.preview: Fired when a tab is attached to a window, for example because it was moved between windows.

class.name: OnDetachedEvent
class.preview: Fired when a tab is detached from a window, for example because it is being moved between windows.

class.name: OnActiveChangedEvent
class.preview: Deprecated. Please use onActivated.

class.name: OnSelectionChangedEvent
class.preview: Deprecated. Please use onActivated.

class.name: TabsOnMovedEvent
class.preview: Fired when a tab is moved within a window. Only one move event is fired, representing the tab the user directly moved. Move events are not fired for the other tabs that must move in response. This event is not fired when a tab is moved between windows. For that, see onDetached.

class.name: OnUpdatedEvent
class.preview: Fired when a tab is updated.

class.name: MostVisitedURL
class.preview: An object encapsulating a most visited URL, such as the URLs on the new tab page.

class.name: TtsVoice
class.preview: A description of a voice available for speech synthesis.

class.name: TtsEvent
class.preview: An event from the TTS engine to communicate the status of an utterance.

class.name: OnSpeakEvent
class.preview: Called when the user makes a call to tts.speak() and one of the voices from this extension's manifest is the first to match the options object.

class.name: ChromeSetting
class.preview: An interface that allows access to a Chrome browser setting. See proxy.settings for an example.

class.name: UploadData
class.preview: Contains data uploaded in a URL request.

class.name: BlockingResponse
class.preview: Returns value for event handlers that have the 'blocking' extraInfoSpec applied. Allows the event handler to modify network requests.

class.name: HttpHeaders
class.preview: An array of HTTP headers. Each header is represented as a dictionary containing the keys name and either value or binaryValue.

class.name: RequestFilter
class.preview: An object describing filters to apply to webRequest events.

class.name: OnAuthRequiredEvent
class.preview: Fired when an authentication failure is received. The listener has three options: it can provide authentication credentials, it can cancel the request and display the error page, or it can take no action on the challenge. If bad user credentials are provided, this may be called multiple times for the same request.

class.name: ChromeEnum
class.preview: The abstract superclass of Chrome enums.

class.name: ChromeApi
class.preview: A common super class for the Chrome APIs.

class.name: ChromeObject
class.preview: The abstract superclass of objects that can hold chrome/dart-js.JsObject proxies.
